<main class="shell page-grid reveal">
  <section class="content-flow">
    <p class="eyebrow">Linux</p>
    <h2>Linux is an open source operating system that is especially important in servers, development, and technical computing.</h2>
    <p>Linux is valued for flexibility, security, and efficiency. Because it is open source, it can be modified and distributed in many forms, which has led to a wide range of distributions.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-flow">
    <h3>Advantages</h3>
    <div class="project-list">
      <article class="project-item"><strong>Open source</strong><p>Its code can be studied, changed, and redistributed, which makes it useful for learning and customization.</p></article>
      <article class="project-item"><strong>Security</strong><p>Linux is often chosen for environments where stability and security are major priorities.</p></article>
      <article class="project-item"><strong>Efficient resource usage</strong><p>Many Linux systems can run well with fewer resources than other desktop operating systems.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-flow statement-band">
    <p class="eyebrow">Popular distributions</p>
    <h3>Different Linux distributions are designed for different users and technical needs.</h3>
    <p>Ubuntu is commonly recommended for beginners, while Red Hat is widely used in enterprise and server environments.</p>
  </section>
</main>

